description._content: Description: Company on patrol. Location: Nyasaland, Somaliland Date: 1922 Description: Company on patrol. Shows me on pony and Lieut, E.P.N.Shirley, Royal Irish Fusiliers, standing by his pony. Location: Nyasaland, Somaliland Date: 1922 Description: Company on patrol. Shirley and myself and senior NCOS. Location: Nyasaland, Somaliland Date: 1922 Description: Company on patrol. Shirley and self busy in the company headquarter shelter. Location: Nyasaland, Somaliland Date: 1922 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/13 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives, uploaded as part of the Africa Through a Lens project. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. Our records about many of these images are limited. If you have more information about the people, places or events shown in an image, please use the comments section below. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
